<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="54" type="synonymy">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Synonymy.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
See 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas, P" journalOrPublisher="E. J. Brill / W. Backhuys, Leiden" pageId="36" pageNumber="85" refId="B76" refString="Kaas, P, Van Belle, RA, 1994. Monograph of living chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) 5, Suborder Ischnochitonina: Ischnochitonidae: Ischnochitoninae (concluded) Callistoplacinae; Mopaliidae; Additions to Volumes 1-4. E. J. Brill/W. Backhuys, Leiden" title="Monograph of living chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) 5, Suborder Ischnochitonina: Ischnochitonidae: Ischnochitoninae (concluded) Callistoplacinae; Mopaliidae; Additions to Volumes 1 - 4" year="1994">Kaas and Van Belle (1994)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="54" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
Regarding its habits, 
<bibRefCitation author="Reid, DG" journalOrPublisher="Zoology" pageId="39" pageNumber="88" pagination="109 - 146" refId="B135" refString="Reid, DG, Osorio, C, 2000. The shallow-water marine mollusca of the Estero Elefantes and Laguna San Rafael, southern Chile. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History). Zoology 66 (2): 109 - 146" title="The shallow-water marine mollusca of the Estero Elefantes and Laguna San Rafael, southern Chile. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History)." volume="66" year="2000">Reid and Osorio (2000)</bibRefCitation>
commented that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sowerby I" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Polyplacophora" family="Ischnochitonidae" genus="Ischnochiton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ischnochiton pusio" order="Chitonida" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pusio">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Ischnochiton pusio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits the lower part of the rocks and other hard substrates in the intertidal zone up to 90 m, with a depth preference between 5 and 30 m in the fjord zones. Consequently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schwabe, E" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="40" pageNumber="89" pagination="1 - 27" refId="B152" refString="Schwabe, E, Foersterra, G, Haeusserman, V, Melzer, RR, Schroedl, M, 2006. Chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) from the southern Chilean Comau Fjord, with reinstatement of Tonicia calbucensis Plate, 1897. Zootaxa 1341: 1 - 27" title="Chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) from the southern Chilean Comau Fjord, with reinstatement of Tonicia calbucensis Plate, 1897." volume="1341" year="2006">Schwabe et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that this species is less tolerant of the fluctuations in salinity, and for that reason, inhabits below the halocline.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
